tspan.tspan: write the same code again and again.
// We just need to create a function for each call.
In the old request, we had to repeat the same code every time. This method is not only
troublesome when coding, but also needs to be modified in each file if there are changes.
This way is not good. In new requests, we encapsulate all requests in the same format and
add necessary specifications (for example, each request must have a token, if not logged in,
it is an empty string.) and verify each response. If the status code is not 200, an error
message will be displayed directly to the user
In the old code, every time we need to return to the front end, we need new Response and
specify parameters. This is inconvenient to code. And it is not a good choice to throw an
exception to the client without exception dealing with. In the new code, the return of all
requests will be processed uniformly. And the format is fixed, which consists of statusCode,
message, and data. The front-end can perform global processing as long as the status code
is not 200. All exceptions will also be handled and then displayed to the user
USER_IS_NOT_EXISTED(20003, "User is not existed or password is incorrect"),
CHECK_TOKEN_FAIL(20004, "Token verification failed, please log in again.")
